		<title>Topaz War Relocation Center</title>
		<link>/2018/06/05/topaz-war-relocation-center/</link>
					<comments>/2018/06/05/topaz-war-relocation-center/#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[josephscott]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2018 16:21:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[history]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[utah]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[video]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">/?p=16676</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Recently we drove down to Delta, Utah to visit the Topaz War Relocation Center. If Topaz doesn&#8217;t sound familiar, you might know it by another term. It was a Japanese internment camp. This is something we&#8217;ve talked about doing for awhile, and now that some of the kids are a little older, it felt like [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Recently we drove down to <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Delta,+UT+84624/@39.3547367,-112.6117015,13z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x874cb4f1fc5b1441:0x33bd538c873c82c2!8m2!3d39.3521777!4d-112.57717">Delta, Utah</a> to visit the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topaz_War_Relocation_Center">Topaz War Relocation Center</a>.  If Topaz doesn&#8217;t sound familiar, you might know it by another term.  It was a <a href="https://www.history.com/topics/world-war-ii/japanese-american-relocation">Japanese internment camp</a>.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16680" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/history-maya.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p>This is something we&#8217;ve talked about doing for awhile, and now that some of the kids are a little older, it felt like the right time.  It is important that the next generation have something tangible to remember about the era of Japanese internment in the United States.  I was able to hear first hand accounts from people I&#8217;ve known who were in the internment camps in their youth.  As time goes on, that is going to happen less and less.</p>
<p>The location of the camp itself is mostly empty desert now.  One square mile of open land, with very little to see.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16682" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-empty.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p>In one corner of the old camp there are three markers and an American flag.  The location is now a U.S. National Historic Landmark.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16686" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-markers.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16687" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-1.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16688" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-2.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16689" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-marker-3.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16691" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/topaz-wire.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p>The <a href="http://www.topazmuseum.org/">Topaz museum</a> is in the small town of Delta, and it is a must visit if you are down there.  It has a wonderful setup.  Among the many items in the museum is the camera that Dave Tatsuno used to document a few aspects of life in the Topaz camp.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16693" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-1-1200x900.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16694" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-2-1200x900.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="630" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16695" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3-300x225.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3-768x576.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2018/06/camera-3-1200x900.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px" /></a></p>
<p>Because of the historical significance of the film it is now part of the Library of Congress.  You can also find it on Youtube.</p>
<a href="/2018/06/05/topaz-war-relocation-center/"><img src="/wp-content/plugins/wp-youtube-lyte/lyteCache.php?origThumbUrl=%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FKboirnCzius%2Fhqdefault.jpg" alt="YouTube Video"></a><br /><br /></p>
<p>You will see many smiling faces, Tatsuno indicated that people were trying to put on a happy face to hide the pain and sorrow.</p>
<p>Topaz really does feel like the middle of no where.  It is a vast empty space, with a strong wind that makes it difficult to hear a person next to you speaking.  I can&#8217;t imagine be forced to live there, under armed guard ( one person was shot and killed for getting too close to the fence ), for three years.</p>
<p>The first step in learning from history is to remember it.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
					<wfw:commentRss>/2018/06/05/topaz-war-relocation-center/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
			<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
		
		
